      • TTSession

        public TTSession(java.lang.String earthModel,
                 double sourceDepth,
                 java.lang.String[] phases,
                 boolean allPhases,
                 boolean returnBackBranches,
                 boolean tectonic,
                 boolean useRSTT,
                 boolean isPlot)
          throws java.io.IOException
        Construct up a session from the session parameters
        Parameters:
        earthModel - Like ak135
        sourceDepth - Depth in km
        phases - List of phase desired or null for all phases
        allPhases - If true all phase return (this is !useful for the TT package)
        returnBackBranches - Return back branches (TT this is !noBackBranch)
        tectonic - source is a tectonic province
        useRSTT - Use RSTT instead for all local phases
        isPlot - Call in plot mode
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If unable to read auxiliary or travel-time information

      • newSession

        public void newSession(double latitude,
                       double longitude,
                       double depth,
                       java.lang.String[] phList,
                       boolean allPhases,
                       boolean backBrn,
                       boolean tectonic,
                       boolean rstt,
                       boolean plot)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        Set up a new session. Note that this sets up the complex session parameters of use to the travel-time package.
        Parameters:
        latitude - Source geographical latitude in degrees
        longitude - Source longitude in degrees
        depth - Source depth in kilometers
        phList - Array of phase use commands
        allPhases - This is passed to the TT package as useful = !allPhases
        backBrn - This is passed to the TT package at noBackBranches = !backBrn
        tectonic - in a tectonic region
        rstt - If true, use RSTT for local phase
        plot - If true, call in ploc mode
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If the depth is out of range
